<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>Thy Kingdom Come</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done
 On earth, on earth... just as it is in Heaven.
 Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done
 Right here on earth... just as it is in Heaven.

[V2]
 Jesus left His perfect home in Heaven;
 Sent from the Father to seek and to save the lost.
 And Jesus said, &quot;As the Father sent me, so I send you...
 If you would be my disciples you must count the cost!&quot;
 Because it's no small thing that I gave you my life,
 I want your passions crucified to the world.
 It's not enough to just get through;
 You are my witnesses in all that you do!

[V3]
 Thy Kingdom come...

[V4]
 I've given you my commandment
 To reach the ends of the earth;
 The nations of the world are on my Father's heart.
 But I require your life, your soul, your possessions...
 Even your children;
 Every child of God, I expect you to do your part!
 Lord give us the workers who will obey Your Word,
 For nearly half the world has still not heard.
 Oh may Your Church hear Your voice today,
 And spread the Gospel through the earth we pray...
 Thy Kingdom come...</lyrics>
<hymn_number>3457</hymn_number>
<author>Scott Alan</author>
</song>